<FIRST>r a PM-BoxOffice     04-11 0431</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Box Office,0451</SECOND>
<HEAD>`Major League' Leads Off In First Place</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JOHN HORN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>HOLLYWOOD (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   ``Major League,'' the story of a big-league
baseball team inherited by a showgirl, hit a home run in its first
time at bat at the nation's box offices.
   The Paramount movie starring Tom Berenger as a washed-up catcher
on the team took in $8 million last weekend to finish at the top of
the box office rankings by Exhibitor Relations Co.
   Three other new releases finished among the top six movies last
weekend.
   Universal's ``The Dream Team,'' a comedy about four mental
patients in New York, debutted in second place with $5.7 million.
   ``Rain Man,'' winner of four top Oscars, continued its strong
post Academy Awards-showing by gathering $4.1 million to finish in
third place.
   Another newcomer, ``Cyborg,'' starring Jean-Claude Van Damme as
``the first hero of the 21st century,'' finished fourth on receipts
of $3.1 million.
   ``Fletch Lives,'' a comedy sequel featuring Chevy Chase, landed
in fifth with $2.6 million. Next was ``Dead Calm,'' a new thriller
set on a sailboat, with sales of $2.4 million. In seventh was the
re-release of ``The Rescuers,'' with $1.7 million.
   ``Lean on Me,'' the dramatization of the life of high school
principal Joe Clark, finished in eighth with $1.5 million.
   Completing the top 10 were the comedy ``Bill and Ted's Excellent
Adventure,'' with $1.4 million and the bedroom drama ``Dangerous
Liaisons,'' with $1.1 million.
   Here are the top movies for last weekend as tallied by Exhibitor
Relations, with distributor, weekend gross, number of theater
screens, average per screen, total gross and number of weeks in
release.
   1. ``Major League,'' Paramount, $8.8 million, 1,541 screens,
$5,734 per screen, $8.8 million, one week.
   2. ``Dream Team,'' Universal, $5.7 million, 1,316 screens,
$4,335 per screen, $5.7 million, one week.
   3. ``Rain Man,'' United Artists, $4.1 million, 1,580 screens,
$2,604 per screen, $148.6 million, 16 weeks.
   4. ``Cyborg,'' Cannon, $3.1 million, 830 screens, $3,831 per
screen, $3.1 million, one week.
   5. ``Fletch Lives,'' Universal, $2.6 million, 1,473 screens,
$1,770 per screen, $27.2 million, three weeks.
   6. ``Dead Calm,'' Warner Bros., $2.4 million, 959 screens,
$2,569 per screen, $2.4 million, one week.
   7. ``The Rescuers,'' Disney, $1.7 million, 1,463 screens, $1,172
per screen, $16.2 million, four weeks.
   8. ``Lean on Me,'' Warner Bros., $1.5 million, 904 screens,
$1,703 per screen, $25.9 million, five weeks.
   9. ``Bill and Ted's Excellent Adventure,'' Orion, $1.4 million,
1,201 screens, $1,171 per screen, $33.7 million, seven weeks.
   10. ``Dangerous Liaisons,'' Warner Bros., $1.1 million, 622
screens, $1,788 per screen, $29.2 million, 15 weeks.
</TEXT>
