   The government has won convictions of
four Puerto Rican nationalists in a $7.1 million heist. But the
militants' supporters claimed victory, saying the trial will help
the island gain independence.
   The four have maintained that the trial stemming from one of the
country's biggest cash heists was politically motivated. They and
