<FIRST>r a PM-MacheteAttack     04-11 0299</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Machete Attack,0305</SECOND>
<HEAD>Police Kill Disturbed Man On Crowded Street</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By VIRGINIA BYRNE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A deranged man swinging a machete-like knife on
a busy street was shot to death by police after a stun gun failed
to stop him.
   The hulking man with a mohawk haircut kept screaming, ``You're
going to have to kill me or I'm going to kill you!'' during the
rampage Monday in midtown Manhattan, said Officer Richard O'Neill
of the Patrolmen's Benevolent Association.
   ``They all did cartwheels to prevent having to shoot him,''
O'Neill said. ``The guy just wanted to die and nothing was going to
stop him.''
   The man, who carried no identification, swung an 18-inch knife
at pedestrians and scared a passerby into dropping his briefcase
and fleeing into a building before five police officers arrived,
police said.
   One officer sprayed Mace at the man but missed his face, police
said. A policeman fired two darts from a 50,000-volt stun gun, but
one apparently missed and the other may have failed to penetrate
his four shirts, they said.
   An officer shot the man twice from about three feet after he
twice lunged at the policeman with the knife, O'Neill said. The
victim, who was about 6 feet tall and around 200 pounds, died an
hour later, police said.
   Police said the man wielded a Gurkha knife with an angled steel
blade and a worn wooden handle. Gurkhas are warriors from the
mountains of Nepal known for their ferocity in battle. Their knives
can be purchased in stores in the city.
   Separately, police charged two men with assault and cocaine
possession in a machine-gun attack on a grocery store late Monday
that left six people wounded, one critically. Police said they had
no motive for the shootings.
</TEXT>
