<HEAD>Tire Theft Leads to Slaying, Police Say</HEAD>
<DATELINE>POMONA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man who tried to steal the tires from a
parked car was shot to death Tuesday by the car's enraged owner,
police said.
   Arnold Lloyd, 47, was being held without bail for investigation
of murdering Michael Stephenson, 20, of Pomona.
   Lloyd confronted Stephenson about 2 a.m. outside his home as
Stephenson tried to steal the tires, police said.
   Stephenson leaped into the bed of a friend's pickup truck and
was being driven away when Lloyd fired a .22-caliber revolver once,
said police Sgt. Elias Valdez.
   Police found Stephenson not far away with a gunshot wound in the
back. Doctors at Pomona Valley Hospital Medical Center were unable
to revive him.
