<FIRST>r w AM-QuayleTrip     04-11 0154</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Quayle Trip,150</SECOND>
<HEAD>Quayle to Visit Australia, Singapore, Indonesia, Thailand</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Vice President Dan Quayle will visit
Australia, Singapore, Indonesia and Thailand over a 10-period from
April 26 to May 5, aides said Tuesday.
   Quayle will represent President Bush at this year's celebration
of Australian-American Friendship Week, which symbolizes the
historically close relations between the two countries and
commemorates the Battle of the Coral Sea during World War II, in
which U.S. and Australian forces overcame great odds to gain a
military victory.
   While in the country, Quayle and his wife, Marilyn, will meet
with Austrialians ``from all walks of life'' during visits to
Canberra, Melbourne and Sydney, according to a statement
distributed by aides.
   The trips to Indonesia, Singapore and Thailand _ like the one to
Australia _ will take special note of the membership of these
countries in the Association of Southeast Asian Nations and in the
U.S. alliance.
</TEXT>
