<FIRST>u i AM-AuschwitzConvent     04-11 0308</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Auschwitz Convent,0321</SECOND>
<HEAD>Israel Asks Poland To Help Remove Auschwitz Convent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Foreign Minister Moshe Arens appealed Tuesday
to a visiting Polish Cabinet minister to press for removal of a
Roman Catholic Carmelite convent from the site of the Auschwitz
death camp, officials said.
   In Geneva, the European leader of the Jewish organization B'nai
B'rith said in a telephone interview that Jewish-Catholic relations
will remain frozen until the convent is gone.
   Jewish and Roman Catholic leaders agreed in February 1987 in
Geneva to transfer the convent's 14 nuns to a new location by
February 1989. Their declaration recognized the special
significance of Auschwitz to Jews.
   Some of the 6 million Jews who died in the World War II Nazi
Holocaust were killed at Auschwitz in southern Poland.
   Ernst Ludwig Ehrlich, European Director of B'nai B'rith, said
Tuesday, however, ``resistance by the Catholic rank-and-file and
others in all of Poland'' has prevented progress toward fulfilling
the Geneva pact. He was one of the signatories.
   Moreover, he called three crosses placed at the site by the nuns
last fall a ``clear provocation.''
   He said no new site had been picked for the order and that no
blueprint had been drawn up, despite reported intervention by Pope
John Paul II. The convent has been at Auschwitz since 1984.
   In Jerusalem, Arens met with Polish Minister of Religious
Affairs Wladyslav Loranc and told him ``the continued presence of
the Carmelite convent on that site causes very strong pains and
indignation in Israel,'' Foreign Ministry officials said.
   Arens told Loranc he hoped the government of Poland would find a
way to put the 1987 agreement into effect, said the Israeli
officials, who spoke on condition of anonymity.
   Polish officials made no comment.
   Loranc is spending eight days in Israel as an official guest of
Israel's minister of religion, Zevulun Hammer.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
