<SECOND>AM-Quake-Puerto Rico,110</SECOND>
<HEAD>Quake Hits Puerto Rico</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A moderate earthquake shook eastern Puerto
Rico and the Virgin Islands on Tuesday evening, according to the
U.S. Geological Survey.
   The quake, measured at 4.3 on the Richter scale, was felt
throughout the capital of San Juan, the eastern half of the island,
and the neighboring Virgin Islands, said USGS spokeswoman Pat
Jorgenson.
   There were no immediate rports of damage, she said.
   The quake's epicenter was in the Caribbean Sea, 50 miles of San
Juan, she said.
   The Richter scale is a gauge of the energy released by a quake.
A temblor of magnitude 4 can cause moderate damage in populated
areas.
