<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   U.S. mergers and acquisitions fell sharply in
the first quarter of 1989 compared with the frenzy of last year,
but experts say the figures are misleading and the outlook for more
takeovers is good.
   Mergers and corporate transactions announced during the first
quarter fell to 340 from 412 in the same period of 1988, according
to statistics made available Monday by Securities Data Co., a
Newark, N.J., research firm.
