<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Paper     04-11 0108</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Paper,0114</SECOND>
<HEAD>International Paper Earnings Rise 40 Percent in First Quarter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   International Paper Co. said Tuesday its
first-quarter earnings rose 40 percent as the paper products firm
enjoyed growth in all its businesses.
   International Paper said earnings for the first three months of
the year totaled $223 million, or $1.96 per share, up from $159
million, or $1.38 per share, in the same period a year earlier.
   Sales rose to $2.6 billion from $2.3 billion in the first
quarter of 1988.
   Company chairman John Georges said International Paper's major
markets, reprographic paper, containerboard, bleached board and
market pulp, remained strong during the quarter.
</TEXT>
